"We are a small team working like a close family and we will miss him dearly," the spokesman added.
Our thoughts and condolences are with Frank's family and friends at this difficult time.
Louis Galicia said that Frank initially lived in hostels, but that "things finally went uphill for him."
"He found an apartment, he had a girlfriend," Louis Garcia told KGO.
Louis Galicia said he could not imagine anyone wanting to harm his younger brother.
He was a kind person with a big heart.
His way of connecting with his family was always to cook us something, to make us dinner, "Louis Galicia said.
He never wanted to be involved in any kind of altercation.
He was the brother who swam with the river.
