Her latest collaboration, "A Decent Meal," to be published Tuesday by Harper's, chronicles the history of American cuisine during the Great Depression.
They showed culinary solidarity when they met with a reporter for dinner at Eisenberg's Sandwich Shop, a small, no-frills takeaway in the Flatiron District that has been in business since the stock market crash of 1929.
