Baden-Württemberg: Police investigate snack bar after rocker attack
After an attack on an Ulm snack bar, the police are investigating six suspects from the rocker milieu for serious breach of the peace.
Evidence and drugs were seized during searches of homes, police said on Friday.
Around 20 masked men from a rocker-like group had thrown bottles and stones at the window of a takeaway in July, according to police.
They then allegedly attacked two guests and slightly injured one.
They then fled.
Damage to the snack bar and the adjacent building amounted to 10,000 euros.
According to the investigators, it is about an argument in the Ulm rocker milieu between a Kurdish and a Turkish gang.
Thuringia: Zeiss Meditec has moved closer to the billion-euro turnover
High demand for medical technology in Asia has boosted Carl Zeiss Meditec's sales.
In the first nine months of the financial year, which began in October, consolidated sales rose by 6.7 percent to 798.6 million euros, the listed company announced on Friday in Jena.
The Asian business grew disproportionately by 17.1 percent.
Earnings before interest and taxes rose from 89.5 million euros to 110.5 million euros, according to the interim balance sheet.
The Jena-based medical technology group intends to exceed the turnover mark of one billion euros in this financial year, the Executive Board confirmed.
Zeiss Meditec manufactures devices and equipment for medical practices and clinics.
The company, which belongs to the optics and electronics group Carl Zeiss (Oberkochen), employs almost 3000 people.
